column5: Never seen or heard of this before. There are three pics. http://www.flickr.com/photos/tinyfishy/1917034552/
Impressive shots, worthy of the 16 hours spent by the photographer.
the nerves of that mother osprey!!!couldn't she take off with a 13lbs walleye instead.  OOOPPPPSSSSSS   Cool pictures for sure.
Looks like the spotted musky (Great Lakes Musky) in Lake St. Clair.
Doesn't she know not to use a verticle hold on those fish?
I don't think that was 54". why wouldn't she throw it back?
